latestIgtvVideos.title: Everyday with changes you can make!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I love my everyday make up takes me about 5 to 7 Mins to do, what I love about this is that you can choose to apply the eye liner or not, you can choose to apply the lipstick or not so many variations I share in this. 
These are the products I use daily - 
Step 1 - Moisture Surge by @clinique_in mixed with Suncreen @larocheposay 50+spf
Step 2 - @maccosmeticsindia Steobe cream I'm using golden
Step 3 - Eyes - eye shadow pallet by @maccosmeticsindia
Semi-Sweet Times Nine
Step 4 - Eyeliner  @myglamm black Jet set eyes Kajal Eyeliner / Killer Kajal by @toofacedlovesindia / @maccosmeticsindia Stubborn Brown
If you want to use a mascara @bobbibrownindia Smokey Eyes Mascara
Step 5 - Cakeless concealer by @benefitindia
Step 6 - Foundation by @diorbeauty Forever Undercoverage 24H Full Coverage 
Step 6 - compact powder @armanibeauty Luminous Silk Compact
Step 7 - Bronzer 
Step 8 - Highlighter by @maccosmeticsindia Soft & Gentle 
Step 9 - Lip Balm, Lip Pencil Soar or Spice by @maccosmeticsindia
Step 10 - @maccosmeticsindia lipstick Faux 
Step 11 - @smashboxindia Photofinish Spray

latestIgtvVideos.title: Fragile X Syndrome
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Fragile X Syndrome (FXS) is the most common inherited single gene cause of intellectual disability and autism worldwide. In India @fragilexindia is working towards this cause to spread awareness for this cause and is also helping families with the similar problems come together to share experiences and resources. Do check out this live conversation with Shalini Kedia the founder of @fragilexindia and Help Spread Awareness!

latestIgtvVideos.title: AI - Artificial Intelligence by @codingandmore
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
AI is all around us. It’s in our smartphone - the facial recognition to the photo tagging. Our Gmail too tells us what to respond in our mail. Amazon recommends what we should buy, Netflix recommends what we can watch, even Instagram suggests who else we may like to follow.

With us and our children being on a connected device AI is shaping the way we perceive the world. 

Which is why it’s important for us to learn how AI works and how we can use it more responsibly.

In this demo by @codingandmore kids learn how to make a facial recognition app. 

Relevant and world class curriculum for children directly from MIT media labs, IBM AI certified teachers and children safe platforms. 

Make your child Future ready. Start your learning today in small personalized batches. Call 9820450891 to book your class.
